    {
        "content": "<p>Should <code>by</code> have the  \"don't capture any more variables\" semantics that <code>theorem</code> has?</p>",
        "id": 506612234,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1742347123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No need for Mathlib here:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">-- we don't mention this in the proof, so we can ignore it</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">not_used</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">omit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not_used</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ohno</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PLift</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">FermatLastTheorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">--suggests `exact not_used.elim`, which also works</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This seems like <code>omit</code> doesn't do what it says on the box, it doesn't remove variables for <code>def</code>s.</p>",
        "id": 506612990,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Meiburg",
        "timestamp": 1742347543
    },
    {
